\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Formula $f:\,\mathbb{R}\rightarrow\mathbb{R},$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $f(x)=\cos x,$
\end_inset

 jest jednostajnie ciągła - 
\begin_inset Formula $\forall_{\epsilon>0}\exists_{\delta>0}\forall_{a\in D}\forall_{x\in D}|x-a|<\delta\implies|f(x)-f(a)|=|\cos x-\cos a|=|-2\sin\frac{x-a}{2}\sin\frac{x+a}{2}|=2|sin\frac{x-y}{2}||\sin\frac{x+y}{2}|\le2|\frac{x+y}{2}|\cdot1=|x-y|<\epsilon$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Więc wystarczy wybrać 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta=\epsilon$
\end_inset


